00:22:10.270 --> 00:22:14.790
So, post demo, there's
a couple of important

00:22:14.790 --> 00:22:18.780
implications of this
for developers as

00:22:18.780 --> 00:22:20.610
well for input tools.

00:22:20.610 --> 00:22:24.240
The first of these is that you
never know what tools people

00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:27.700
might be using to enter text
into your website or into your

00:22:27.700 --> 00:22:28.390
application.

00:22:28.390 --> 00:22:31.000
So specifically, they
may be using

00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:32.320
this Input Tools extension.

00:22:32.320 --> 00:22:35.150
They may be using a client
site IME of some kind.

00:22:35.150 --> 00:22:38.540
Or they may be using other
accessibility tools, like

00:22:38.540 --> 00:22:41.330
Chrome Box, to read what's on
the screen, or what's in a

00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:43.660
text box, or know where
a text box is.

00:22:43.660 --> 00:22:45.730
And so it's very important
that when you build

00:22:45.730 --> 00:22:48.350
applications, particularly web
applications but also Android

00:22:48.350 --> 00:22:51.310
applications, that you're using
standard components and

00:22:51.310 --> 00:22:55.540
standard pieces of HTML and
don't do anything terribly

00:22:55.540 --> 00:22:59.970
fancy with input boxes, with
editable DIVs, so that these

00:22:59.970 --> 00:23:03.190
tools will work for users not
just within the US and Europe,

00:23:03.190 --> 00:23:05.140
but also for users
around the world.

00:23:05.140 --> 00:23:09.210
The second key takeaway for
developers is that you don't

00:23:09.210 --> 00:23:11.720
really know what types of
content are coming into your

00:23:11.720 --> 00:23:13.650
application or where they're
coming from.

00:23:13.650 --> 00:23:16.680
So you may be getting all types
of content, in all kinds

00:23:16.680 --> 00:23:21.550
of languages, in all kinds of
encodings, where you may not

00:23:21.550 --> 00:23:22.530
have designed it for that.

00:23:22.530 --> 00:23:24.500
So it's important for
applications to be built from

00:23:24.500 --> 00:23:28.240
the ground up supporting Unicode
and assuming Unicode

00:23:28.240 --> 00:23:31.810
is coming into the application
and processing all of the

00:23:31.810 --> 00:23:35.930
strings in any other aspects of
what the application does

00:23:35.930 --> 00:23:38.420
assuming Unicode
and in Unicode.

00:23:38.420 --> 00:23:40.670
So from the developers'
perspective, there's a lot of

00:23:40.670 --> 00:23:42.730
other things that need to go
into an application to ensure

00:23:42.730 --> 00:23:44.360
that technologies like
these work for

00:23:44.360 --> 00:23:46.581
users around the world.

