00:23:49.420 --> 00:23:50.940
So up to this point,
we have looked at

00:23:50.940 --> 00:23:54.180
internationalization, what it
entails, what does the global

00:23:54.180 --> 00:23:56.710
design look like, global
architecture looks like.

00:23:56.710 --> 00:23:58.210
And then, we have also
looked at some other

00:23:58.210 --> 00:23:59.900
internationalization tools.

00:23:59.900 --> 00:24:03.290
Now, let's do the same
for localization.

00:24:03.290 --> 00:24:05.560
First of all, here are the five
points that you would

00:24:05.560 --> 00:24:09.420
need to do for localization
irrespective of what you're

00:24:09.420 --> 00:24:09.990
localizing.

00:24:09.990 --> 00:24:11.590
So it could be your
Android apps.

00:24:11.590 --> 00:24:12.840
It could be your Chrome maps.

00:24:12.840 --> 00:24:14.200
It could be a website.

00:24:14.200 --> 00:24:19.520
It could be your static
files documents.

00:24:19.520 --> 00:24:21.900
First of all, you need
to determine your

00:24:21.900 --> 00:24:22.940
target language set.

00:24:22.940 --> 00:24:25.570
And again, that's a very
important decision

00:24:25.570 --> 00:24:26.430
that needs to happen.

00:24:26.430 --> 00:24:29.150
And again, that may change
over time as well.

00:24:29.150 --> 00:24:31.440
We will talk about some of the
considerations for that in our

00:24:31.440 --> 00:24:33.540
next slide.

00:24:33.540 --> 00:24:37.040
Second is separating localizable
resources from

00:24:37.040 --> 00:24:37.770
your source code.

00:24:37.770 --> 00:24:40.500
And again, we saw on the global
architecture design,

00:24:40.500 --> 00:24:42.930
that was essentially the
third set of boxes.

00:24:42.930 --> 00:24:46.030
And that is very critical for
you to essentially have a good

00:24:46.030 --> 00:24:47.140
localized experience.

00:24:47.140 --> 00:24:50.100
You don't own hard-coded strings
in your application to

00:24:50.100 --> 00:24:52.100
show up, especially when
people are accessing in

00:24:52.100 --> 00:24:54.130
different languages.

00:24:54.130 --> 00:24:57.620
The third aspect is test
your application for

00:24:57.620 --> 00:25:00.120
localizability issues.

00:25:00.120 --> 00:25:05.170
How do you know whether it's
ready for actual localization?

00:25:05.170 --> 00:25:08.010
You would essentially at the
point when you are ready for

00:25:08.010 --> 00:25:12.360
translation, you should not
require any re-engineering or

00:25:12.360 --> 00:25:13.290
code changes.

00:25:13.290 --> 00:25:15.800
In that case, we have taken
care of most of the

00:25:15.800 --> 00:25:17.390
localizability issues.

00:25:17.390 --> 00:25:21.230
And so the localization tools
are really your friend here at

00:25:21.230 --> 00:25:22.750
this point for that.

00:25:22.750 --> 00:25:26.000
If those tools can help you
find problems like text

00:25:26.000 --> 00:25:29.530
swirling, hard-coded strings,
not handling accented

00:25:29.530 --> 00:25:33.870
characters, even before you
actually do the localization.

00:25:33.870 --> 00:25:37.010
And again, we would highly
encourage you to use that

00:25:37.010 --> 00:25:40.680
phase in terms of your
pseudolocalization.

00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:44.500
The fourth is you will choose
a localization vendor.

00:25:44.500 --> 00:25:47.860
And either them or you will
choose the localization tool

00:25:47.860 --> 00:25:48.720
that you use.

00:25:48.720 --> 00:25:51.410
Important consideration for
localization tools are, it

00:25:51.410 --> 00:25:54.040
should have advanced
technologies like translation

00:25:54.040 --> 00:25:55.910
memory, glossary, and so on.

00:25:58.710 --> 00:26:01.800
As we've talked in the previous
slide, let's talk a

00:26:01.800 --> 00:26:06.600
little bit more about the key
considerations that you have

00:26:06.600 --> 00:26:09.410
when deciding which locale, a
combination of your country

00:26:09.410 --> 00:26:13.850
and location, you would like
to have your app or your

00:26:13.850 --> 00:26:16.260
product available in.

00:26:16.260 --> 00:26:18.300
Broadly, the considerations
could be

00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:20.120
divided into two types.

00:26:20.120 --> 00:26:23.780
One is the key matrix based
on various key metrics.

00:26:23.780 --> 00:26:25.890
And again, there could
be a variety of them.

00:26:25.890 --> 00:26:28.250
And the second is based on
the effort required for

00:26:28.250 --> 00:26:31.470
implementation of these.

00:26:31.470 --> 00:26:33.960
So let's talk more about
the key metrics.

00:26:33.960 --> 00:26:35.830
So again, there could be a
variety of different key

00:26:35.830 --> 00:26:40.480
metrics that you could base your
decision in terms which

00:26:40.480 --> 00:26:43.110
countries or which languages
to go after.

00:26:43.110 --> 00:26:45.180
You could essentially
decide based on top

00:26:45.180 --> 00:26:46.820
languages used on the web.

00:26:46.820 --> 00:26:49.770
You could essentially base it on
top countries by cell phone

00:26:49.770 --> 00:26:53.220
usage, top countries by
paid app installed.

00:26:53.220 --> 00:26:55.690
You could essentially go by
what my competitor offers.

00:26:55.690 --> 00:26:59.650
If competitor is localized in 15
languages, you might do the

00:26:59.650 --> 00:27:00.720
same as well.

00:27:00.720 --> 00:27:02.210
And then, finally, there
could be some

00:27:02.210 --> 00:27:04.380
app-specific metric as well.

00:27:04.380 --> 00:27:07.110
So for example, if you are a
game developer, you might want

00:27:07.110 --> 00:27:13.650
to go by the top countries
by paid game downloads.

00:27:13.650 --> 00:27:15.040
So let's say we picked one.

00:27:15.040 --> 00:27:18.670
We go by top languages
used on the web.

00:27:18.670 --> 00:27:20.400
And we localize in
10 languages.

00:27:20.400 --> 00:27:22.780
So you essentially pick the
top 10 languages on the

00:27:22.780 --> 00:27:26.220
internet and say, OK, I will
localize in those.

00:27:26.220 --> 00:27:27.480
Question for the audience?

00:27:27.480 --> 00:27:30.970
What is the percentage of users
you can cover if you

00:27:30.970 --> 00:27:31.740
essentially do that?

00:27:31.740 --> 00:27:35.560
You would essentially localize
your app in top 10 languages.

00:27:35.560 --> 00:27:37.825
