I want now my app to be in

00:29:11.420 --> 00:29:13.810
German, Spanish, and so on.

00:29:13.810 --> 00:29:16.270
The second is the ability
to search in those

00:29:16.270 --> 00:29:18.100
languages in your app.

00:29:18.100 --> 00:29:19.860
And for that, you need
language detection

00:29:19.860 --> 00:29:20.850
mechanism as well.

00:29:20.850 --> 00:29:24.040
So with those, you can pretty
much try and target the Latin

00:29:24.040 --> 00:29:24.820
script languages.

00:29:24.820 --> 00:29:27.480
You will probably need some
bit of testing as well.

00:29:27.480 --> 00:29:31.280
The next set of languages that
you can target are non-Latin,

00:29:31.280 --> 00:29:32.530
European languages.

00:29:32.530 --> 00:29:36.480
These would include languages
like Russian, Ukrainian,

00:29:36.480 --> 00:29:41.010
Serbian, and Greek.

00:29:41.010 --> 00:29:43.340
In addition to what we described
for Latin script

00:29:43.340 --> 00:29:45.990
languages, there are added
complexities in terms of

00:29:45.990 --> 00:29:48.710
transliteration is important
for these languages.

00:29:48.710 --> 00:29:50.960
Plus for languages
like Serbian, the

00:29:50.960 --> 00:29:55.270
interchangeability between the
Latin script keyboards and the

00:29:55.270 --> 00:29:59.130
Cyrillic keyboards becomes
an important aspect

00:29:59.130 --> 00:30:00.680
to consider as well.

00:30:00.680 --> 00:30:03.190
The next set of languages
are the CJK--

00:30:03.190 --> 00:30:06.440
