is the font size.

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:13.270
You need to take care of that
because characters typically

00:30:13.270 --> 00:30:15.540
tend to be bigger in size.

00:30:15.540 --> 00:30:17.490
The second is the display
mechanism might change.

00:30:17.490 --> 00:30:21.470
So some of these languages are
displayed vertically as well.

00:30:21.470 --> 00:30:23.990
And the third aspect is input.

00:30:23.990 --> 00:30:26.340
So input method iterators become
an important aspect.

00:30:26.340 --> 00:30:26.950
Why?

00:30:26.950 --> 00:30:30.410
Because just the enormous
number of

00:30:30.410 --> 00:30:32.760
characters in these languages.

00:30:32.760 --> 00:30:35.840
The next set of languages are
the South and Southeast Asian

00:30:35.840 --> 00:30:39.980
languages, specifically
Thai and Hindi.

00:30:39.980 --> 00:30:42.880
They are typical because
you need to handle

00:30:42.880 --> 00:30:46.090
the contextual display.

00:30:46.090 --> 00:30:49.330
Characters in these languages
essentially change based on

00:30:49.330 --> 00:30:50.690
the context.

00:30:50.690 --> 00:30:52.450
And the second important
aspect is the size

00:30:52.450 --> 00:30:53.250
segmentation.

00:30:53.250 --> 00:30:57.430
So in Thai, where the words
are not separated by wide

00:30:57.430 --> 00:31:00.690
space, you need to take care of,
especially from a search

00:31:00.690 --> 00:31:01.750
perspective, how the

00:31:01.750 --> 00:31:03.680
segmentation is done correctly.

00:31:03.680 --> 00:31:06.410
And the last of languages are
the bi-directional languages,

00:31:06.410 --> 00:31:10.420
which include Arabic, Hebrew,
Persian, Urdu.

00:31:10.420 --> 00:31:12.930
And these are really the most
challenging languages from

00:31:12.930 --> 00:31:14.540
engineering perspective.

00:31:14.540 --> 00:31:16.910
Why are these called
bi-directional languages?

00:31:16.910 --> 00:31:20.580
Mainly because the text flows
from right to left and the

00:31:20.580 --> 00:31:23.520
numbers go from left to right.

00:31:23.520 --> 00:31:26.080
Special attention is needed
for the user interface,

00:31:26.080 --> 00:31:27.330
especially in those languages.

